-- tedw_release_summary
VALUES (
'
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <span style="background-color: #9D0208; color: white; font-weight: bold; font-size: 18px; padding: 5px; display: inline-block; text-decoration: underline;">Release Summary - 04/21/2025 :</span>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 0;font-style: italic;color: blue;">This release had 5 enhancements and 20 bug fix tickets.  Release details are as follows.</h4>
    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; }
        h1, h2 { color: #333; }
        ul { margin: 10px 0; padding-left: 20px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h2 style="font-style: italic;">1. EDW/Datamart Enhancements</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Added the following premium mod columns in tauto_vehicle_coverage and tquote_auto_vehicle_coverage tables:
            <ul>
                <li>added_first_party_premium_adjustment_amount</li>
                <li>added_first_party_premium_adjustment_method</li>
                <li>added_first_party_premium_adjustment_reason</li>
                <li>added_first_party_premium_adjustment_retention</li>
                <li>added_personal_injury_protection_premium_adjustment_amount</li>
                <li>added_personal_injury_protection_premium_adjustment_method</li>
                <li>added_personal_injury_protection_premium_adjustment_reason</li>
                <li>added_personal_injury_protection_premium_adjustment_retention</li>
                <li>basic_first_party_premium_adjustment_amount</li>
                <li>basic_first_party_premium_adjustment_method</li>
                <li>basic_first_party_premium_adjustment_reason</li>
                <li>basic_first_party_premium_adjustment_retention</li>
                <li>customized_premium_adjustment_amount</li>
                <li>customized_premium_adjustment_method</li>
                <li>customized_premium_adjustment_reason</li>
                <li>customized_premium_adjustment_retention</li>
                <li>fire_premium_adjustment_amount</li>
                <li>fire_premium_adjustment_method</li>
                <li>fire_premium_adjustment_reason</li>
                <li>fire_premium_adjustment_retention</li>
                <li>property_protection_insurance_premium_adjustment_amount</li>
                <li>property_protection_insurance_premium_adjustment_method</li>
                <li>property_protection_insurance_premium_adjustment_reason</li>
                <li>property_protection_insurance_premium_adjustment_retention</li>
                <li>theft_premium_adjustment_amount</li>
                <li>theft_premium_adjustment_method</li>
                <li>theft_premium_adjustment_reason</li>
                <li>theft_premium_adjustment_retention</li>
                <li>uninsured_bodily_injury_premium_adjustment_amount</li>
                <li>uninsured_bodily_injury_premium_adjustment_method</li>
                <li>uninsured_bodily_injury_premium_adjustment_reason</li>
                <li>uninsured_bodily_injury_premium_adjustment_retention</li>
                <li>uninsured_motorist_premium_adjustment_amount</li>
                <li>uninsured_motorist_premium_adjustment_method</li>
                <li>uninsured_motorist_premium_adjustment_reason</li>
                <li>uninsured_motorist_premium_adjustment_retention</li>
                <li>uninsured_property_damage_premium_adjustment_amount</li>
                <li>uninsured_property_damage_premium_adjustment_method</li>
                <li>uninsured_property_damage_premium_adjustment_reason</li>
                <li>uninsured_property_damage_premium_adjustment_retention</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Updated stored procedure logic to populate missing premium mods (blanket_premium_adjustment_method, blanket_premium_adjustment_factor, blanket_premium_adjustment_retention, blanket_premium_adjustment_retention_reason, scheduled_premium_adjustment_method, scheduled_premium_adjustment_factor, scheduled_premium_adjustment_retention, scheduled_premium_adjustment_retention_reason) in tcollection_class_type and tquote_collection_class_type tables  for home/condo policies which had collections coverage</li>
        <li>Updated stored procedure logic to populate missing premium mods (premium_adjustment_method, premium_adjustment_factor, premium_adjustment_retention, premium_adjustment_retention_reason) in thome_coverage and tquote_home_coverage tables</li>
        <li>Updated stored procedure logic to load missing payment_approver_nm and payment_approver_dt in tclaim_payment table</li>
        <li>Updated stored procedure logic to accurately assign claim feature status in tclaim_transaction table</li>
        <li>Updated the stored procedure logic to align the roof deck attachment value with the Metal display value in both in thome_coverage and tquote_home_coverage tables</li>
        <li>Updated the stored procedure logic to align the AdditionalPIP, BasicPIP, BILimit, DeductibleAppliesTo, UIMLimit, UMLimit, UMBIPolicyLimit and WorkLossExclusion value in both tauto_policy_coverage and tquote_auto_policy_coverage tables</li>
        <li>Updated stored procedure logic to populate certain fields (policy_effective_dt, policy_sk, product_sk, underwriting_company_nm, broker_id, customer_id) associated with litigation claims in tclaim table</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="font-style: italic;">2. EDW Process Enhancements</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Updated stored procedure logic to support long labels for LC360 vendor report</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="font-style: italic;">3. EDW Integrations</h2>

    <h3>a. Workday Enhancements</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Updated claim payment, reserves, and reserves ITD file to remove entries for litigation claims</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>b. Ivans</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>VI-37323/VI-36873/VI-37337/VI-37336: Resent IVANS policies</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>c. Hubspot</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>VI-36789: Fixed quote notes to remove special character that we get from Metal before displaying it in Hubspot</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Fixes</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>VI-34518: Updated missing construction type for 16 records in Metal and EDW by pulling it from prior term</li>
        <li>VI-35404: Updated missing loss date in Metal using loss date from prior policy / CLUE data</li>
        <li>VI-34053: Updated incorrect address line 1 associated with 11 policies in Metal and EDW</li>
        <li>VI-37356: Updated status to quoted; policy number was assigned to the original submission, and a commercial submission created in error was closed</li>
        <li>VI-37355: Updated BCEG Credit percent for HO200036580, HO100245003-06, HO200033170 in Metal and EDW</li>
        <li>VI-34699: Updated garaging zip code associated with AU100031429 in Metal and EDW</li>
        <li>AD9210: Updated claim C24AUA00804 and C24AUA01026 to correct the total loss incurred, which was impacted by adjuster’s cancellation of an approved payment transaction</li>
    </ul>
</body>
'
,'Yes'
,'2025-04-21'
,getdate()
,getdate()
)
;

-- tedw_release_note
